description:
Romanian project with big existing team is looking for a Romanian-speaking senior php developer with experience in Symfony4 and above.
Please only apply if: full-time (8h/day) is possible from may and you can start with at least 6h/day on 15march. 
PHP Requirements&nbsp;&nbsp;-Senior Level:
&bull; Experience in developing web applications (at least 4-5 years);
&bull; Extensive experience with PHP and SQL (MySQL, PostgreSQL, or SQL Server);
&bull; Good understanding of MVC frameworks (Symfony 4 or newer) and application architecture patterns;
&bull; Knowledge of front-end concepts (HTML, CSS, JavaScript);
&bull; Experience with caching systems of any sort but preferable: Redis;
&bull; Familiar with monitoring tools such as Kibana, New Relic, PMM or Grafana;
&bull; Familiar with queueing systems such as RabbitMQ;
&bull; Knowledge of web services (RESTful / SOAP), JSON, XML, web servers (Apache / Nginx), containers (Docker, Kubernetes), Linux, and communication protocols;
&bull; Good interpersonal and teamwork skills;
&bull; Interest in continuous career development;
Ability to express your thoughts in English (written or spoken).<b>Skills</b>:        Symfony,                     PHP,                     Symfony 4,                     MySQL

We have Virtual Server configured with Virtual Server IP:Port = external IP address:443. This IP:Port also used for Fortigate ACME Let&#039;sEncrypt certificate (we run a small webserver for internal use). Therefore, we would like a automated script to:
1) 30 days from Let&#039;sEncrypt certificate expiry date (at set at 2359 hours);
2) temporarily change Virtual Server Port to some other port;
3) check that Let&#039;sEncrypt certificate has successfully retrieved new certificate (it should show new expiry date);
4) change back Virtual Server Port to 443.<b>Skills</b>:        FortiGate Firewall,                     Linux
